          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-05 22:12:46.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-05 22:33:49.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 llite: fix IT_WRITE_LEASE intent handling crashes",
        "message": "LU-0000 llite: fix IT_WRITE_LEASE intent handling crashes\n\nFix kernel crashes when processing IT_WRITE_LEASE intents by\nadding proper support in the LMV and MDC layers.\n\nThe crashes occurred because the LMV layer didn't handle\nIT_WRITE_LEASE in lmv_intent_lock() and the MDC layer didn't\nset proper lock policy bits for IT_WRITE_LEASE operations.\n\nThis patch adds IT_WRITE_LEASE to the lmv_intent_lookup() path\nin the LMV layer, adds an IT_WRITE_LEASE case in the\nmdc_finish_intent_lock() switch statement, and sets\nMDS_INODELOCK_UPDATE policy bits for IT_WRITE_LEASE operations.\n\nThese changes ensure IT_WRITE_LEASE intents are properly routed\nthrough the intent lock infrastructure without causing kernel\npanics due to unhandled intent types.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I38c21d97ccadd309930612491a2c67029460eb21\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
